My professional capabilities and strengths include:

 

   1. Computer Illustration: Proficient in computer illustration techniques and workflows, and skilled in using software such as Photoshop, Procreate, UDMpaint, AI, C4D, SAI, Blender, and Processing for digital art and design. Experienced in using drawing tablets and graphic tablets for drawing, with extensive training in line art, color balancing, lighting and shading, sketching techniques, character design, and human anatomy. Notable works include the "Furry" illustration collection, "Dragging Skirt" illustration collection, "Breakfast, Lunch, Dinner" graphic design portfolio, "Two Brothers" comics, book cover design for "Stories from the Riverbank Plain," character illustrations for personal game projects, promotional artwork for personal game projects, and the generative art collection "Starry Sky after a Rainy Night."

 

2. Arts and Crafts: Proficient in creating artistic pieces using glass as a medium. Knowledgeable in glass kiln firing, lampworking, glass fusing, glass inlay, mosaic collage, ornamental carving, glass blowing, as well as pottery techniques like coil construction, wheel throwing, and glaze formulation. Created several art pieces, and achieved outstanding results with glass sculptural artworks "Ice Box" and "Frost Point" at the graduation exhibition, selected by Henan Zero Contemporary Art Company for participation in their organized art exhibition "Boundaries That Don't Exist."

 

3. Art Education: Qualified to be a high school art teacher, possessing knowledge in art disciplines, educational studies, and educational psychology. Previously involved in volunteer teaching activities during the tenure as the Propaganda Committee member of the Luxun Academy of Fine Arts Youth League.

 

4. Language Proficiency: Proficient in English, capable of fluent conversation and communication. Passed academic language tests equivalent to an overall IELTS score of 6.5.

Some of my personal hobbies include:

 
1. Drawing and Painting: I enjoy expressing my creativity through drawing and painting. It allows me to relax, explore new techniques, and bring my imagination to life.
 
2. Reading: I am an avid reader and enjoy immersing myself in different genres of literature. Books broaden my perspective and inspire my artistic endeavors.
 

3. Traveling: Exploring new places and experiencing different cultures is a great source of inspiration for my artwork

Practical Experience:

In 2018, I was appointed as an external counselor for the "Big Hands Holding Little Hands, Growing Together" volunteer teaching program jointly organized by Luxun Academy of Fine Arts Dalian Campus and Longshan Elementary School. I worked as a part-time volunteer teacher for one year during my time at the academy.
